<body>
  <div id="game-container"></div>
  <div id="rotate-prompt" aria-hidden="true">
    <svg width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <rect x="14" y="4" width="20" height="40" rx="3" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="2" fill="none"/>
      <path d="M40 20 L44 24 L40 28" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="2" fill="none"/>
      <path d="M36 24 L44 24" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="2"/>
    </svg>
    <span>ROTATE DEVICE</span>
  </div>
  <a href="#privacy" class="privacy-link">Privacy Policy</a>
  <div class="scroll-hint" onclick="document.getElementById('info').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth'})"><span>▼ SCROLL DOWN FOR INFO ▼</span></div>

  <main class="info-wrapper" id="info">
    <div class="info-inner">

      <!-- About -->
      <section class="info-section" id="about">
        <h2>About Gulf Guardian</h2>
        <p>Gulf Guardian is a free tactical naval escort game set in the Strait of Hormuz. You command the USS Guardian DDG-117, an Arleigh Burke-class destroyer, tasked with escorting a convoy of three oil tankers through one of the world's most dangerous waterways.</p>
        <p>Navigate contested waters, engage hostile forces, and protect your convoy across five increasingly dangerous sectors. The game features a retro phosphor-green CRT monitor aesthetic inspired by classic naval radar displays.</p>
        <p>No download required. Gulf Guardian runs entirely in your browser using WebGL.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Features -->
      <section class="info-section" id="features">
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Five sectors of increasing difficulty through the real Strait of Hormuz</li>
          <li>Six enemy types: Fast Attack Boats, Coastal Missile Batteries, Gunboats, Drones, Attack Helicopters, and Sea Mines</li>
          <li>Combo kill system with multipliers up to 8x and streak milestones: RAMPAGE, UNSTOPPABLE, GODLIKE, LEGENDARY</li>
          <li>Full arsenal: MK-45 deck gun, RGM-84 Harpoon missiles, Phalanx CIWS, radar, countermeasures, and ramming</li>
          <li>Retro phosphor-green CRT monitor aesthetic with scanlines, vignette, and screen effects</li>
          <li>Desktop keyboard/mouse and mobile touch controls</li>
          <li>No accounts, no downloads, no ads during gameplay</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Controls -->
      <section class="info-section" id="controls">
        <h2>Controls</h2>

        <h3>Desktop</h3>
        <dl class="controls-grid">
          <dt>WASD</dt>
          <dd>Move ship</dd>
          <dt>ARROWS / LMB</dt>
          <dd>Fire deck gun</dd>
          <dt>SPACE / RMB</dt>
          <dd>Launch missile (auto-targeting)</dd>
          <dt>SHIFT / X</dt>
          <dd>Speed boost</dd>
          <dt>R</dt>
          <dd>Ram</dd>
          <dt>ESC / P</dt>
          <dd>Pause</dd>
        </dl>

        <h3>Mobile</h3>
        <dl class="controls-grid">
          <dt>LEFT STICK</dt>
          <dd>Move ship</dd>
          <dt>RIGHT STICK</dt>
          <dd>Aim and fire guns</dd>
          <dt>MISSILE BUTTON</dt>
          <dd>Launch missile</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section class="info-section" id="faq">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is Gulf Guardian?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Gulf Guardian is a free retro-style tactical naval escort browser game. You command a destroyer escorting oil tankers through the Strait of Hormuz while defending against hostile boats, missiles, mines, drones, and helicopters. It features a distinctive phosphor-green CRT aesthetic and fast-paced arcade action.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I play Gulf Guardian?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Use WASD to move your destroyer and arrow keys or left-click to fire your deck gun. Press Space or right-click to launch homing missiles. Your objective is to escort three oil tankers safely through five sectors of the Strait of Hormuz while destroying enemy threats. Chain kills to build combo multipliers and maximize your score.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is Gulf Guardian free to play?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes, Gulf Guardian is completely free to play. There are no in-app purchases, subscriptions, or paywalls. The game runs directly in your browser with no download or account required.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Which browser should I use?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Google Chrome is recommended for the best performance. Firefox, Edge, and Safari are also supported. The game requires a modern browser with WebGL support. Make sure your browser is up to date for the best experience.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can I play on mobile or tablet?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes! Gulf Guardian supports mobile and tablet devices in landscape orientation. The game uses virtual joysticks and on-screen buttons optimized for touch controls. For the best experience, rotate your device to landscape mode.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Why isn't the game loading?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Make sure your browser supports WebGL and that hardware acceleration is enabled. Try refreshing the page, clearing your browser cache, or switching to Chrome. If you're on an older device, the game may take a moment to load assets. Check that JavaScript is enabled and no browser extensions are blocking the game.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>The game is running slowly. How can I fix it?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Try closing other browser tabs and applications to free up system resources. Make sure hardware acceleration is enabled in your browser settings. Chrome typically offers the best performance. On lower-end devices, the game automatically adjusts quality settings to maintain smooth gameplay.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What types of enemies are in the game?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Gulf Guardian features six enemy types: Fast Attack Boats that chase your tankers at high speed, Coastal Missile Batteries hidden along the Iranian coastline, heavily armed Gunboats with multi-missile spreads, fast-moving aerial Drones, Attack Helicopters that engage from range, and Sea Mines planted in the shipping channel. Each type requires different tactics to counter effectively.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Does Gulf Guardian work on Chromebooks?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes, Gulf Guardian works on Chromebooks. The game is optimized for browser-based play and automatically adjusts graphics quality based on your device's capabilities. Chrome OS provides excellent WebGL support for smooth gameplay.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What weapons and abilities does the player have?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Your Arleigh Burke-class destroyer is equipped with a MK-45 5-inch deck gun for rapid fire, RGM-84 Harpoon missiles that auto-target enemies, a Phalanx CIWS point defense system, speed boost for evasive maneuvers, and the ability to ram smaller vessels. You carry 12 missiles per mission, so use them wisely against high-value targets.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I report a bug or give feedback?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>You can report bugs or share feedback by visiting <a href="https://bluewizard.com" rel="noopener">bluewizard.com</a>. We appreciate all reports and suggestions to help improve the game.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    &copy; 2026 Blue Wizard Digital. All Rights Reserved. | <a href="#privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
  </footer>

  <footer class="privacy-footer" id="privacy">
    <div class="privacy-footer-inner">
      <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: March 20, 2026</p>

      <h3>Overview</h3>
      <p>Gulf Guardian is a free browser-based game. We respect your privacy and aim to be transparent about what data is collected when you visit our site.</p>

      <h3>Information We Collect</h3>
      <p>We do not require user accounts, registrations, or personal information to play the game. The following data may be collected automatically:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Standard web server logs (IP address, browser type, pages visited)</li>
        <li>Device and browser information for game compatibility</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Advertising</h3>
      <p>We use Google AdSense and other third-party advertising partners to display ads. These partners may use cookies and similar technologies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this and other websites. Specifically:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Google uses cookies to serve ads based on your visit history. You can opt out of personalized advertising at <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a>.</li>
        <li>Third-party vendors and ad networks listed in our <a href="/ads.txt">ads.txt</a> file may collect and use data to serve relevant ads.</li>
        <li>You can visit <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" rel="noopener">aboutads.info</a> to opt out of third-party cookies used for personalized advertising.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Cookies</h3>
      <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device. This site may use cookies for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Advertising delivery and frequency capping</li>
        <li>Analytics and performance measurement</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may affect ad delivery but will not impact gameplay.</p>

      <h3>Third-Party Services</h3>
      <p>This site may use the following third-party services that have their own privacy policies:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Google AdSense — <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li>Google Fonts — for typography rendering</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Children's Privacy</h3>
      <p>This site is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

      <h3>Changes to This Policy</h3>
      <p>We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected on this page with an updated date.</p>

      <h3>Contact</h3>
      <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy, please reach out via our website.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script>
    // Toggle scroll hint and privacy link visibility based on scroll position
    (function() {
      var ticking = false;
      window.addEventListener('scroll', function() {
        if (!ticking) {
          requestAnimationFrame(function() {
            document.body.classList.toggle('scrolled-past-fold', window.scrollY > window.innerHeight * 0.25);
            ticking = false;
          });
          ticking = true;
        }
      });
    })();
  </script>
  <script type="module" src="/src/main.ts"></script>
</body>
</html>
